Nigerian Agency, NDLEA Operatives Invade Comedian's House, Brutalise Him In Viral Video
0 Comments
12 Hours Ago In the clip, the victim appeared to be challenging the NDLEA officials for invading his house while also filming the incident. But one of the officials had asked him to stop the video, claiming the comedian had no right to film them. The man, however, insisted on filming the incident, a development which made the NDLEA officials to attack the man. Spokesperson for the NDLEA, Femi Babafemi, said the comedian was arrested for drug-related issues. “He (Martins) was arrested because drugs were found in his house. A detailed statement will be issued shortly.”